Admirabar amplius quarn enuncio. (The short text of the Incendium follows. The initial “Admirabar'' is com- bined with a shield [argent‚ a cross gules charged with an escutcheon, or, possibly, with bordure, and cinquefoil in centre]. The chapters are not numbered, but marked with beautiful initials. Writing very clear, with few contractions. The scribe was evidently intelligent; he frequently emended the grammar where the other short texts do not differ, and where, from the variation in the MSS„ the original text must have been obscure; his variant is generally more grammatically correct than that of the others.
